<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="U" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Umpire" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Umpire,</orth> one to whose arbitration a question is referred: <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.1.139" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. I, 1, 139</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 1.1.170" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL I, 1, 170</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.1.151" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A IV, 1, 151</bibl>. Applied to death as the general peace-maker: <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.5.29" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 5, 29</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 4.1.63" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. IV, 1, 63</bibl>.
